    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini Dei aeterni. <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/79"
                            >Hugo</persName> et <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/72"
                            >Lotharius</persName> divina providente clementia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">reges</rs>. Regalem decet exellentiam iustis
                        fidelium petitionibus adsensum prebere. Quocirca omnium fidelium sancte Dei
                        Ecclesie nostrorumque presentium ac futurorum devotio noverit, qualiter <rs
                            key="#Intercessory">interventu ac petitione</rs>
                        <persName key="#Intercessory #Count #fidelisOf"><name ref="Ildericus"
                                >Ilderici</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comitis</rs> dilectique <rs key="#fidelisOf">fidelis</rs>
                        nostri, prout iuste et legaliter possumus, per hoc nostre confirmationis
                        precepta confirmamus ac corroboramus <persName key="#fidelisOf"><name
                                ref="Bernardus">Bernardo</name></persName> nostro <rs
                            key="#fidelisOf">fideli</rs> omnes res proprietatis sue iuste et
                        legaliter adquisitas et adquirendas, sive familias emptionis commutationis
                        vel quolibet titulo legalis scriptionis sibi pertinentes. Insuper concedimus
                        ei per hunc nostrum regale preceptum <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals #Churches"
                            >Sancti Salvatoris</orgName> cum <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terris</rs> et <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>, <geogName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fines"><rs key="#Fines">finis</rs>
                            Arole</geogName> et <geogName key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fines"
                            >Ariole</geogName> et <geogName key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fines"><rs
                                key="#Fines">finis</rs> Alpis</geogName> locis; simul cum rebus
                        illis qui sunt in <placeName key="#Uncertain_tradition" ref="#places/2779"
                            >Carda</placeName>, in <placeName key="#Uncertain_tradition"
                            >Prata</placeName> et in <placeName key="#Uncertain_tradition"
                            >Casalae</placeName> et res illa in <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition" ref="#places/2777">Blatiano</placeName>;
                        simul et cum rebus illis in <geogName key="#Uncertain_tradition"
                            >Manditiano</geogName> et eius pertinentia, quibus nobis per <rs
                            key="#Cartula">cartula</rs> obvenit da quondam <persName><name
                                ref="Winigildus">Vuinegildo</name></persName>; res ille in
                            <placeName key="#Uncertain_tradition" ref="#places/2778"
                            >Campriano</placeName>, <placeName key="#Uncertain_tradition"
                            ref="#places/2777">Blatiano</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition">Fabriciano</placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition" ref="#places/2780">Cerreta</placeName>, qui
                        fuerunt de <rs key="#Curtes">corte</rs> nostra <geogName key="#Curtes"
                            ref="#estates/2385"><placeName ref="#places/2781">Caput
                                Leonis</placeName></geogName>, vel per singula loca et vocabula
                        regni nostri de ipsis rebus adiacentibus; recipientes eundem Bernardum et
                            <rs key="#childOf">filios suos</rs> sub nostre <rs
                            key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">tuitionis mundburdum</rs> una cum
                        omnibus rebus mobilibus et immobilibus sibi iuste et legaliter
                        pertinentibus, <rs key="#Royal_slave">servis et ancillis</rs>. Precipientes
                        itaque iubemus, ut nullus dux, marchio, comes, vicecomes, seu quelibet regni
                        nostri magna parvaque persona predictum Bernardum molestare vel de suis
                        rebus desvestire audeat, absque legali iudicio. Si quis igitur huius nostri
                        precepti confirmationem seu mundburdi tuitionem aliquando infringere conatus
                        fuerit, sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri optimi libras
                            quinquaginta</rs>, <rs key="#Camera_regis">medietatem camere nostre</rs>
                        et <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem prefato Bernardo
                            suisque heredibus</rs>. Quod ut verius credatur diligentiusque ab
                        omnibus observetur, manibus propriis roborantes anulo nostro insigniri
                        iussimus. Signa serenissimorum (M) (M) Hugonis et Lotharii regum. <persName key="#Chancellor" ref="#people/1535"
                            >Giseprandus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/1531">Bosonis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellari</rs> recognovi et subscripsi. (SR) (SID). Data XII kal.
                        novembris, anno dominice incarnationis DCCCCXLIII, regni vero domni Hugonis
                        XVIII, Lotharii XIII, indictione secunda. Actum <placeName ref="#places/65"
                            >Papie</placeName>. Feliciter.</ab>
